results.name: Number of distinct differences between consecutive divisors (ordered by increasing magnitude) of n which are not also divisors of n.
link: Robert Israel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: For n=70, divisors={1,2,5,7,10,14,35,70}; differences={1,3,2,3,4,21,35}; the differences {3,4,21} are not divisors, so a(70)=3.
program: (PARI) a(n) = my(d=divisors(n)); #select(x->(setsearch(d, x)==0), vecsort(vector(#d-1, k, d[k+1] - d[k]),,8)); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jul 04 2017
results.author: _Labos Elemer_, Apr 24 2001
